  "section_name": "Financial Analysis",
  "text": "R&D investment intensity remains elevated, with Q2 2025 R&D expenses of $610,000,000 representing 19.70% of revenue, indicating continued commitment to platform development and innovation (C007, K005). This represents an increase from prior quarters, with R&D spending of $568,000,000 in Q1 2025, $524,000,000 in Q3 2024, and $519,000,000 in Q2 2024, suggesting escalating investment in technology infrastructure and product capabilities (C014, C021, C028). The rising R&D intensity may pressure near-term margins but positions the company for long-term competitive differentiation in the alternative accommodation marketplace.",
